  "barToBeat": "To move the stock, Apple needs to deliver a revenue beat of at least 2% above consensus, coupled with reassuring guidance on iPhone demand and Services growth, as the buy-side is whispering about potential softness in the iPhone 17 lineup's second-half sales trajectory. The stock is already pricing in a modest EPS beat, so a mere in-line print may not be enough to sustain momentum.",
  "watchPoints": [
    { "title": "iPhone Revenue Growth", "why": "iPhone sales are the primary driver of Apple's revenue, and any signs of slowing growth could impact the stock. The iPhone 17 lineup's performance will be closely watched, particularly in the face of increasing competition from Android vendors.", "metric": "15% YoY growth" },
    { "title": "Services Segment", "why": "The Services segment has been a key growth engine for Apple, and investors will be looking for continued strength in areas like Apple Music, Apple TV+, and Apple Arcade. Any weakness in Services could raise concerns about the company's ability to diversify its revenue streams." },
    { "title": "Gross Margin Guidance", "why": "Apple's gross margin has been under pressure due to component costs and supply chain constraints. Investors will be watching for any changes to the company's gross margin guidance, which could impact profitability and earnings growth. A metric to watch is a gross margin of at least 38.5%.", "metric": "38.5%" }
